;◇チュートリアル・宿泊解説
*tutorial_5

@out t=0
@bg f=tutorial09
@wait time=500
[texton w=1]
[フロント係]「The reservation screen starts with all party members gathered in the inn's lounge. Please drag them all to an empty room.」[r]
[b]∗ Can also be operated with a keyboard[/b].[k]
[フロント係]「Each room has a fixed price and a capacity which can't be exceeded.[r]
In addition, rooms may be unavailable due to reservations by other guests.」[k]
[textoff]

@bg f=tutorial10
@wait time=500
[texton]
[フロント係]「Once everyone has been assigned a room, press the "Stay" button. You will be taken to the night conversation screen.[r]
Please note that if even one member remains in the lounge, check in cannot proceed.」[k]
[フロント係]「If you are short of money, you can still stay, but will have to pay the debt later. (While your balance is negative, you cannot make new purchases, etc.)」[k]
[textoff]

@bg f=tutorial11
@wait time=500
[texton]
[フロント係]「Once you move to the night conversation screen, you can talk with any member. Select the person you wish to converse with.[r]
At this time, events may occur.」[k]
[フロント係]「When you're ready for bed, press the Sleep button. HP and MP will be restored in the morning.」[r]
[b]∗Note that members who stay in the stable won't recover any HP or MP![/b][k]
[textoff]

@bg f=tutorial12
@wait time=500
[texton w=1 top=550]
[フロント係]「Members who have accumulated enough experience level up.[r]
Parameters are increased and new magic is learned.」[k]
[フロント係]「[b]Leveling up can only be done at the inn[/b].[r]
Please note that no matter how much EXP you accumulate, you won't level up unless you stay at an inn. [r]
Also, only one level can be gained per stay.」[k]
[textoff]

[texton]
[フロント係]「That's all for the explanation. Now, please go to the [b]reservation screen[/b] to reserve a room for all members!」[k]
[textoff]
@out
@gameon
[hoteloff]


;◇チュートリアル・隊列解説
*tutorial_6

; 最初のダンジョンに入ったところで
@wait time=500
[if exp='! game.isFreeMode']
	[texton w=5]
	[テオ f=06]「Now that we have more people in the party, let's think carefully about our formation.」[k]
	[textoff]
[endif]

@question title="Would you like to hear an explanation about party formation?"
[eventoff cond='! tf.result']

[texton w=4]
[nw][b blue]About formation[/b][r]
In combat, enemies and allies have a front line and a rear line. Each have different attack ranges. [r]
Allies and enemies with short range weapons can only attack opponents in the opposite front row, and must be in the front row themselves to do so. Anyone in the rear is safe from them.[r]
[b]Long-range attacks (magic, some special attacks) or weapons (bow, spear, etc) can reach other rows and don't require the user to be in the front row. The range of each weapon is different, so please check on the item screen.[k]
[b]Your party's formation can be changed any time outside battle (except for guests). The first 3 members are the front row, and the last 3 are the back.
[b]Guest characters have fixed rows of their own which can't be changed. Enemy parties may have a middle row as well as front and back.[k]
[textoff]
[eventoff]


;◇チュートリアル・アイテム補足説明
*tutorial_7

@command type=long cancel title="Would you like to hear additional information about items?"
@select text="About item weight" target=*_アイテム説明_重量
@select text="Damage and Repair of Items" target=*_アイテム説明_破損
@select text="About unidentified items" target=*_アイテム説明_鑑定
@select text=No target=*_アイテム説明_終了
[s]

*_アイテム説明_重量
@image layer=0 storage=tutorial06 visible=true
[texton w=6]
[nw][b blue]About item weight[/b][r]
There is a limit to the total weight of items that can be equipped.[r]
If equipping an item would exceed that limit, the character can't do so.[k]
[nw]Many heavy items are powerful, but could limit equipping heavier items in other slots, reducing performance there. It's important to strike a balance in this area.[k]
[nw]If the item is only in the inventory rather than equipped, this does not affect the weight limit.[k]
[textoff]
@layopt layer=0 visible=false
@jump target=*tutorial_7

*_アイテム説明_破損
@image layer=0 storage=tutorial07 visible=true
[texton w=6]
[nw][b blue]Damage and Repair of Items[/b][r]
Items may get damaged.[r]
Traps in dungeons and accumulated hits in battle can damage items, breaking or destroying them.[k]
[nw]Damaged items must be repaired, as their performance degrades when in a damaged state, and further damage may destroy them completely.[k]
[nw]Repairs can be made in the following ways:[r]
・[b]Pay a store[/b] to do it for you.[r]
・[b red]Smith[/b], [b red]Alchemist[/b] and other characters with repair skills can do this themselves.
　 [k]
[nw]If you leave it to a Smith or Alchemist party member, a [b]hammer-type weapon[/b] and [b]magic sand[/b] must be available in someone's inventory.[r]
Note that one [b]magic sand[/b] is consumed for each repair.[k]
[textoff]
@layopt layer=0 visible=false
@jump target=*tutorial_7

*_アイテム説明_鑑定
@image layer=0 storage=tutorial08 visible=true
[texton w=6]
[nw][b blue]About item appraisal[/b][r]
You may pick up unidentified items while exploring.[r]
These can be [b]appraised[/b] at a store or by using the [b]Identify command[/b] on the [b]item screen[/b] to find out their identity.[k]
[nw]Unidentified items must be appraised before they can be used or equipped.[r]
[b red]Everyone[/b] can try to appraise, but [b]Bishops, Alchemists, and Sorcerers[/b] are more likely to succeed.[k]
[nw]Note that appraisals by skill are not always successful.[r]
They can fail, break, or put the appraiser in a state of fear.[k]
[nw]Also, if the item you appraise is [b]cursed[/b], you may [b]accidentally equip it[/b] if the appraisal fails.[r]
Be careful when appraising.[k]
[nw][b red]∗Note[/b][r].
Appraisal will be performed by the [b]character[/b] who is in possession of the item. To increase the chance of success, transfer the item to a character with high appraisal skill first.[k]
Please note that items can be appraised while in a treasure chest, but the appraiser will be [b]random[/b].[k]
[textoff]
@layopt layer=0 visible=false
@jump target=*tutorial_7

*_アイテム説明_終了
@question title="Are you sure you want to end the explanation?" cancel
@jump target=*tutorial_7 cond='! tf.result'
[townoff]




;■ポラリスの神殿

;◇イベント01・姫と会話
*shrine_1

; サファイア城
[texton]
[name n=Fiona f=fiona_00]「Welcome to my home. I am Fiona, the King's daughter.」[k]
[name n=Fiona f=fiona_00]「Unfortunately, my father is away from the castle at the moment, so I am fulfilling his duties.」[k]
[name n=Fiona f=fiona_01]「I see that you have accepted my request to the guild. Thank you very much.」[k]
[name n=Fiona f=fiona_02]「I'm most concerned about this. The [b]Temple of Polaris[/b] is being vandalized, and I wish you to stop it!」[k]
[name n=Fiona f=fiona_02]「The temple is dedicated to Polaris, the god of harmony, one of the four great gods of the world. Polaris is revered in this country, so we cannot leave those who would destroy the temple unpunished!」[k]
[name n=Fiona f=fiona_02]「Adventurers, could you please go to the Temple of Polaris and drive out those who are destroying it?」[k]
[name n=Fiona f=fiona_00]「The Temple of Polaris is located northwest of this town, at the end of the first side road after entering Dale Coin Forest. Thank you.」[k]
[textoff]
[otheroff]


;◇イベント02・シュバルツと再会
*shrine_2

; ☆フリーモード
@jump storage="free01.scn" target=*shrine_2 cond='game.isFreeMode'

; 神殿内
@saveon
@fg c=シュバルツ e=通常 f=00
[texton w=1]
[シュバルツ f=00]「Oh...!」[k]
[テオ f=05]「Mr. Schwarz!」[k]
To my surprise, I met Mr. Schwarz again deep in the temple.[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「Fancy meeting you here. What brings you here?」[k]
[テオ f=05]「I'm here at the request of the Princess of Sapphire Castle. Why are you here, Mr. Schwarz? Didn't you retire from being an adventurer?」[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「Yes, I was supposed to, but when I heard that the Temple of Polaris was being raided, I couldn't stand still.」[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「...This temple is an important place dedicated to the god Polaris, who brought peace to this world. We must protect it.」[k]
[テオ f=06]「I didn't know that...」[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「I'd like to ask for your help.」[k]
[テオ f=05]「You would?」[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「You see, many monsters are gathered in the room ahead.」[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「And... one of them is that devil we met before.」[k]
[テオ f=11]「What...?!」[k]
That devil girl I met in the basement of the ruins... Is she up to something again?![k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「They intend to enter the Hall of the Gods ahead and destroy the altar. We must stop them at all costs.」[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「When I see an opportunity, I intend to rush into the room and defeat the monsters. Would you guys be willing to fight with me?」[k]
It is a request from Mr. Schwarz, of all people. We have the same goal, so there's no way we wouldn't agree.[k]
[テオ f=05]「Yes! I'm willing to help!」[k]
[textoff]
@clf
@eval exp='game.guest.entry(o.シュバルツ)'
@se f=period
@notice text="<y>Schwarz joined the party!"
[eventoff]


;◇イベント03・暴れる悪魔の手下たちと戦闘
*shrine_3

; ☆フリーモード
@jump storage="free01.scn" target=*shrine_3 cond='game.isFreeMode'

; 神殿の一室
@saveon
[texton w=0]
[テオ f=05]「...!」[k]
We looked into the room and saw a large number of orcs loitering.[k]
We stay where we are and observe the room.[k]
[テオ f=05]「That's...!」[k]
Beyond the orcs, I spotted a familiar figure.[k]
@mu f=murmur
[悪魔 v=vm026 f=07]「Seriously! Why won't it open?!」[k]
It's that demon...! I thought I'd never see her again...![k]
The demon looks quite frustrated, as if something is not going her way.[k]
[悪魔 v=vm027 f=08]「Grr～! How is this wretched door supposed to open?! I push and pull, and use unlocking magic, but it won't even budge!」[k]
Apparently the demon is really struggling to open the stone door in front of her.[k]
[悪魔 v=vm028 f=07]「That damn god is really pissing me off! There's no way a door should be enough to keep me out!」[k]
; ↑ 「クソ神（くそかみ）」
∗bang!∗[k]
The demon, perhaps considerably annoyed, kicks the hard stone door with hatred.[k]
[悪魔 v=vm029 f=08]「Grr～! If that's how it is, I'll get in there, even if I have to smash through the wall!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm030 f=07]「You lot! Smash through this wall with everything you've got!」[k]
[オーク]「Rrrragh!」[k]
Obeying the demon's orders, all the orcs began to attack the temple walls![k]
They slam their axes and hammers vigorously against the wall, over and over again. The temple shakes slightly, and a sound like a rumbling of the earth echoes throughout the temple.[k]
And... the stone walls began to fall apart due to the destructive activities of these orcs.[k]
[テオ f=08]「Not good...!」[k]
We cannot let them destroy our precious temple. We must stop it...![k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「Let's go, [テオ]!」[k]
[テオ f=05]「Yes!」[k]
[textoff]
@wait time=500
@walk move=n
@walk move=n
@wait time=500
[texton w=1]
[テオ f=07]「Stop!」[k]
@fg c=悪魔 f=06
[悪魔 v=vm031 f=06]「Hmm? Is someone here?」[k]
[シュバルツ f=07]「I will not allow you to desecrate the Temple any further!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm032 f=05]「What? Adventurer! You're not going to get in my way!」[k]
@fgf c=悪魔 f=07
[悪魔 v=vm033 f=07]「...Hmph, it's you guys again～!」[k]
[シュバルツ f=07]「You're up to no good again, devil!」[k]
[テオ f=05]「Stop the destruction of the Temple now!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm034 f=07]「Shut up! Who's going to stop, you idiot! Don't you dare give me orders like that!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm035 f=07]「Orcs! Defeat these disgusting humans!」[k]
@se f=wing1
@fg c=8001 left=440 top=-60
The demon unfurled her wings and soared out of reach.[k]
[オーク]「Rrrragh!」[k]
[テオ f=06]「...!」[k]
Suddenly, all the orcs attack![k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「We'll deal with the demon later! Let's clean up these orcs first!」[k]
[テオ f=07]「Yes!」[k]
[textoff]
@clf

; 悪魔の手下たちと戦闘
@monster pos=0 name=オーク
@monster pos=1 name=オーク
@monster pos=2 name=オーク
@monster pos=3 name=オーク
@monster pos=4 name=オーク
@monster pos=5 name=オーク
@monster pos=6 name=オーク
@monster pos=8 name=オークソルジャー
@monster pos=9 name=オークソルジャー
@monster pos=10 name=オークソルジャー
@monster pos=11 name=オークソルジャー
@monster pos=12 name=オークソルジャー
@callbattle escape=false
; 戦闘に勝利

@mu f=murmur
@fg c=8002 left=440 top=-60
[texton w=1]
[悪魔 v=vm036 f=12]「Wow, seriously? ...Pathetic!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm037 f=08]「Unh～! I hate you～! Seriously, what the hell is wrong with you people!」[k]
The devil, who had been watching the battle from the air, yells her frustration.[k]
[テオ f=07]「I won't let you do whatever you want! I'll never allow you to destroy the temple!」[k]
[シュバルツ f=07]「Get down here, Devil!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm038 f=07]「Hmph! Who the hell would?!」[k]
[テオ f=07]「Why are you attacking this temple?! What do you want?!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm039 f=05]「Huh? This place is dedicated to a god. It's only natural that I, a devil, want to destroy it, isn't it?」[k]
[テオ f=06]「...」[k]
Well, that's certainly not surprising...[k]
[悪魔 v=vm040 f=08]「Besides, Polaris, the god here, was the one who was dumb enough to seal me away in the past!」[k]
[テオ f=05]「What...?」[k]
So the god Polaris has a connection with this devil...?[k]
[悪魔 v=vm041 f=08]「That's why I'm so pissed off! I won't be satisfied unless I get my revenge!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm042 f=06]「There are still other monsters in this world that were sealed away in the previous crusade...」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm043 f=15]「I'm going to set them all free and let them ravage this world! I'm going to ruin everything!」[k]
[テオ f=11]「No... why would you do that?!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm044 f=05]「Huh? I'm a demon. Of course I want to destroy the human world!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm045 f=06]「The world was originally ruled by us demons, you know? Then, the annoying gods and angels sided with you humans and drove the demons out of this world...」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm046 f=15]「That's why I'm going to free all the sealed demons and monsters over the world. Then I'll rule it once again! Get it?」[k]
[テオ f=12]「What the...!」[k]
If that were to happen, this world would be in trouble.[k]
[シュバルツ f=07]「I will not let you and your demons have your way! You won't get away with what you're up to!」[k]
[悪魔 v=vm047 f=15]「If you can, why don't you try it? There's no way you idiots can stop me, though～」[k]
[textoff]
@se f=wing2
@cl
@wait time=500
@walk turn=s
@wait time=500
[texton]
With that, the demon flapped her wings furiously as she headed for the temple exit.[k]
[シュバルツ f=07]「Wait! Don't let it get away!」[k]
@fg c=8002 left=440 top=-60
[悪魔 v=vm048 f=07]「Who the hell is going to get caught by you people! Just die already, you idiot!」[k]
@se f=wing2
@fa
@cl
And with that final retort, she left the temple...[k]
@mu f=shrine
[テオ f=10]「...」[k]
She escaped again... There's nothing you can do if your opponent can fly.[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「What on earth... I can't let this stand.」[k]
[テオ f=06]「...」[k]
It's a big deal... I had no idea that the devil wanted to overthrow the world...[k]
[if exp='game.party.members.has(o.リーゼル)']
	[リーゼル v=vl038 f=05]「Hey, is that the devil you were talking about before...?」[k]
	[テオ f=02]「Yeah, that's right. Despite how she looks, she's really a force to be reckoned with.」[k]
	[リーゼル v=vl039 f=01]「At any rate, I'm glad everyone is safe and sound... Now that we've accomplished what we were asked, why don't we go back to town?」[k]
	[テオ f=02]「Yeah, I guess so.」[k]
	[シュバルツ f=00]「Hmm. There's no point in staying here too long.」[k]
[else]
	[テオ f=06]「...」[k]
[endif]
The demon's movements are worrisome, but we have achieved our initial goal, so let's go back to the town.[k]
[？？？ v=vp001 key=ポラリス noface buf=12]「Adventurers... please come to the altar room...」[k]
[テオ f=05]「?」[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「Hmm? Who are you?」[k]
Suddenly, someone's voice echoed throughout the room.[k]
Who on earth is calling to us?[k]
[？？？ v=vp002 key=ポラリス noface buf=12]「Please come to the altar room...」[k]
[テオ f=06]「...」[k]
[textoff]
@wait time=500
@walk turn=n
@wait time=500
[texton]
The mysterious voice seems to come from behind the closed stone door.[k]
[シュバルツ f=00]「The altar room is the very place the demon was trying to enter earlier. It appears we're being invited inside.」[k]
[テオ f=06]「...」[k]
That said, the stone door is still in the way...[k]
The demon couldn't budge it earlier.[k]
So how do we get to the altar...?[k]
[textoff]
[eventoff]


